'''''Battle of Antietam''''' is a [[computer wargame]] written for the [[Apple II series|Apple II]] by Chuck Kroegel and David Landrey and published by [[Strategic Simulations]] in 1985.<ref name=giantlist/>

==Gameplay==
''Battle of Antietam'' is a game in which the [[Battle of Antietam]] is simulated.<ref name="CGW27"/>

==Reception==
William H. Harrington reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "SSI and the authors have created more than a first rate grand tactical simulation of one of the most critical battles of the Civil War with BOA. They have captured some of the look and 'feel' of Civil War combat, and it shows."<ref name="CGW27">{{cite magazine |last=Harrington |first=William H. |title=Battle of Antietam |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=April 1986 |volume=1 |issue=27 |pages=34â€“35}}</ref>

